members.member:
Move a key line to another position in the header.
The key at this zero-based index will be moved.
/// The key at currentIndex index will be moved to this zero-based index position.

member.param:
Data scaling:
0 = linear;
1 = square root;
2 = squared; 3 = log.

Artificial color mapping: 

0 = grayscale; 

1 = jet; 

2 = winter; 

3 = lines (detects contours and edges).

Pass a single-element array to specify a pre-set contrast limit as per below, or pass a 2-element array to specify the literal contrast limits in terms of standard deviation about the image mean.

Contrast limits:

0 = full range (min to max);

1 = wide (-1 stdv to 2 stdv, stdImclim = [-1, 2]);

2 = dark (-0.5 stdv to 5 stdv, stdImclim = [-0.5, 5]);

any other single-element value throws an exception.

Data scaling: 

0 = linear; 

1 = square root; 

2 = squared; 

3 = log.

Artificial color mapping: 

0 = grayscale; 

1 = jet; 

2 = winter; 

3 = lines (detects contours and edges).

The initial and return parameters of the Gaussian. If p is only initialized and input with all zeros, initial estimates will automatically be computed.
p[0] = amplitude;
p[1] = x-center;
p[2] = sigma;
p[3] = bias.

The initial and return parameters of the tranformation. Options are

p[0] = scale; p[1] = phi (radians); p[2] = x-axis pixel coordinate reference; p[3] = y-axis pixel coordinate reference;

or

p[0] = Matrix coeff [0, 0]; p[1] = Matrix coeff [1, 0]; p[2] = Matrix coeff [0, 1]; p[3] = Matrix coeff [1, 1]; p[4] = x-axis pixel coordinate reference; p[5] = y-axis pixel coordinate reference;

The initial and return parameters of the tranformation. Options are

p[0] = scale; p[1] = phi (radians); p[2] = x-tran pixel coordinate rotation reference; p[3] = y-tran pixel coordinate rotation reference; p[4] = x-tran pixel coordinate shift; p[5] = x-tran pixel coordinate shift;

or

p[0] = Matrix coeff [0, 0]; p[1] = Matrix coeff [1, 0]; p[2] = Matrix coeff [0, 1]; p[3] = Matrix coeff [1, 1]; p[4] = x-tran pixel coordinate rotation reference; p[5] = y-tran pixel coordinate rotation reference; p[6] = x-tran pixel coordinate shift; p[7] = x-tran pixel coordinate shift;

The parameters of the Gaussian.
p[0] = amplitude;
p[1] = x-center;
p[2] = sigma;
p[3] = bias

The parameters of the Moffat:
p[0] = amplitude;
p[1] = x-center;
p[2] = theta;
p[3] = beta;
p[4] = bias

The parameters of the Moffat. Options are:

p[0] = amplitude; p[1] = x-center; p[2] = y-center; p[3] = theta; p[4] = beta; p[5] = bias;

or

p[0] = amplitude; p[1] = x-center; p[2] = y-center; p[3] = phi; p[4] = x-theta; p[5] = y-theta; p[6] = beta; p[7] = bias;
